# Nuxt SSG Conventions

## Directory layout (Nuxt 4)

- App code lives under `app/` (`app.vue`, `pages/`, `components/`, `composables/`, `assets/`)
- Root keeps `nuxt.config.ts`, `public/`, `package.json`
- `~/` and `@/` alias to `app/`; `~~/` and `@@/` alias to project root
- Do **not** create `server/` or Nitro route handlers

## Pages & composition

- Keep `app.vue` and `pages/*` thin: layout shell + feature composition
- File-based routing under `app/pages/`
- Use `useSeoMeta` / `useHead` on every public page
- Prefer `NuxtLink` for internal links so prerender crawl discovers routes
- Wrap browser-only APIs/widgets in `<ClientOnly>` with a sensible fallback

## Data & state

- Prefer build-time data (imports, JSON, CMS fetch during generate)
- `useAsyncData` / `useFetch` only when the request succeeds at generate time
- Avoid `import.meta.server` branches that assume a live Node server in production
- Values like `new Date()` are frozen at generate time — intentional for SSG

## Config

- `nitro.preset: 'static'` and `routeRules['/**'].prerender: true` stay on
- Add new public routes to the site graph (linked) or to `nitro.prerender.routes`
- Deploy artifact: `.output/public`
